Sentencas: The electrolyte/anode interface in solid oxide fuel cells with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolytes and composite anodes containing La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-delta and Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta (GDC) was studied using transmission electron microscope Z-contrast imaging and energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy.
Titulo: Operational Inhomogeneities in La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ Electrolytes and La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Composite Anodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anode/electrolyte interface of an operated cell had numerous defective regions in the electrolyte, immediately adjacent to anode GDC particles.
Titulo: Operational Inhomogeneities in La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ Electrolytes and La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Composite Anodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These areas had a different chemical composition than other electrolyte regions and were crystallographically inhomogeneous.
Titulo: Operational Inhomogeneities in La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ Electrolytes and La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Composite Anodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These regions were not observed in a cell reduced in hydrogen that was not operated, suggesting that they were the result of combined electrical and chemical potential gradients present during cell operation.
Titulo: Operational Inhomogeneities in La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ Electrolytes and La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Composite Anodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ru nanoparticles were observed on the chromite surfaces of the operated.
Titulo: Operational Inhomogeneities in La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ Electrolytes and La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.82Ru0.18O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Composite Anodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
